  "prompt": "[SPOLIERS]Are all the Children of the Forest dead?",
  "response": "Yes, within the context of the TV series \"Game of Thrones,\" it appears that the Children of the Forest are all extinct. This conclusion is drawn after discovering that Leaf, who is one of the last known Children of the Forest, sacrificed herself to protect Bran and Meera from the wights in Season 6. There is no indication that any of the Children survived beyond this event in the show. However, since George R.R. Martin's book series \"A Song of Ice and Fire\" remains unfinished, there is still potential for different information or revelations in the books compared to the TV adaptation.",
